The paper deals with solving separable convex programs, which is a common problem in machine learning. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses convergence results and optimization techniques, which are relevant to numerical analysis (cs.NA) and distributed computing (cs.DC). The use of parallel splitting and optimization for sparse representation and low-rank recovery problems suggests that the paper may also be relevant to computer vision (cs.CV) and control systems (cs.SY).
